<br>
Please note:<br>
<br>
Priests work differently from pure casters and pure meleers/hybrids    <br>
<br>
A priest's function is to aid/defend the people around them.   Sometimes this means they have to heal, sometimes this means they have to take up arms or cast offensively to get their job done.  This is why they have a melee skill over 150 and even higher casting skills and self buffs that are there for the emergency melee session.   It makes no sense to place them in the same sentance as a ranger/monk/rogue.  <br>
<br>
Next note:  <br>
<br>
Monks have been tanking for way too long....<br>
They are there for extreeme, fast damage.. not to stand there and get hit over long periods of time.. same with rogues which dont use their poison skills enough from what I've seen.   <br>
<br>
Rangers are the supreme archers of Norrath.. why aren't they using their archery skill more often?<br>
<br>
You realize that in a really good fight it makes the most sense to have pure casters behind the healers when possible (which would be behind the archers) and the rest of the classes ought to be up close with the mob.   <br>
Reason for this is Armorclass/resistances.  [there are items that increase the range of spells now.. hint,hint]<br>
-----------------------------<br>
Once I had the honor of standing next to a ranger that was root/shooting and discovered that he did 3 times the amount of damage that my spell did in the time that I was casting the spell... (I was a druid of nearly the same level then)  Archery is a lot more powerful that people realize. <br>
<br>
------------------<br>
Regarding the healing spell nerf... <br>
<br>
No matter what.. they is NO Alternative to a cleric. <br>
They are and allways will be the rulers of the healing classes. <br>
<br>
And so far as the &quot;what druids really want&quot; statement goes...<br>
<br>
Original manual for everquest states that a druid must CHOOSE whether they are going to use thier hands or their magic more in a fight... if they plan on using their hands they should go for stamina.. if they plan on using their magic they should go for wisdom.  Not every druid is set up with 115 wisdom, not every druid plans on pretending to make up for the empty cleric spot.   So please... get your head out of that dark place and take some real time to study the class before you mouth off like that like oh say... the THREE+ YEARS that I've spent. <br>
<br>
