<br>
I don't like summoning arrows for half an hour during the cursed fight; I don't like summoning mod rods for a half an hour for that fight either.  It's the same for the other 20-30 minute fights in Luclin, but the 10 minute AoW fight is intense.. and moderately enjoyable after 10 or so kills.<br>
<br>
I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> love</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> what rods allow me to do in exp groups; when the healer has a clue, and the tank has decent weapons, I am chain nuking with a rain ae on top of it, that's out of my spec, on nearly every pull.  There is absolutely no down-time outside of waiting on pulls.  It doesn't bother me much that druids have better nukes, because my most redeeming quality of hp to mana conversion is so fucking effective.  And they are taking it away, because of a mild annoyance on raids.<br>
<br>
It's axiomatic that no one would enjoy bequeathing his or her mana for the boss fight, in entirety, to someone else.  But the fact that is necessary, that you MUST HAVE MAGE<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>S</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> for almost every Luclin encounter gives me a feeling I hold dearly: Importance.<br>
<br>
With mod rods, the raid's success (MT, and ramp tank both living) falls in my hands as the clerics' primary source of mana regeneration – the mages' are in complete control the raid's mana.<br>
<br>
Without mod rods, I'm a third-rate damage dealer on raids.  I won't even be able to profit mana from eating rods anymore on a significant level.<br>
<br>
Fuck VI.  I've started making corpses with rods on them.. maybe the nerf won't be retroactive. I want to keep my mod rods. <p><center>
